; native-translation-loopback.form — the locale's translations become the body's own.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-14):
;   "add chinese and japanese as core concept / node / cell / web-chrome locales so that
;    we can use those translations as training material for our native Form translations."
;
;   The deep shape: a third-party translator is the BOOTSTRAP oracle; its output is BOTH
;   the locale bundles AND the training material; a native Form recipe learns from it and,
;   once proven, carries the pair itself — the oracle->native->A/B->retire pattern the body
;   already runs for speech (TTS<->STT) and vision, turned toward language.
;
; THE BODY ALREADY HELD EVERY PART BUT ONE (read first, compose, do not duplicate):
;   - i18n.fk loads the locale bundles (en + de/es/fr/id/pt-br, zh/ja when added) as a
;     PARALLEL CORPUS — the training data, ~2019 keys per tongue.
;   - the locale system auto-discovers from files: a locale is web/messages/<code>.json +
;     cli/lib/messages/<code>.json; the manifest, middleware, API, and CLI all find it.
;   - loopback-learning.fk is the oracle->native loop (a French->Form lane already runs).
;   - champion-challenger.fk + colearning-retire.fk are the A/B-and-retire arc (parity-
;     first, jit-oracle-learning.form): the native takes a pair only when it reaches the
;     oracle over a window.
;   - meaning-translation-receipt.fk is the proof contract (axiom / encoder / equivalence
;     witnesses; refuse, do not fabricate).
;   - cjk-channel.fk proves a character is ONE cell read in many tongues — translation as
;     content-addressing, not a lookup table.
;
; THE MISSING CELL, NOW BUILT  (form-stdlib/translation-learn.fk -> tests/translation-learn-band.fk 1111111, four-way)
;   The native translation recipe that joins them: (translate pair src) looks up the
;   target from learned pairs (no oracle call); honest absence where it has not learned;
;   meaning preserved by content-addressing — the source and target name ONE cell
;   (cjk-channel: mountain == shan == yama); and tl-promote? (champion-challenger) retires
;   the oracle for a pair when the native reaches it. Seeded from cjk-channel's six
;   attested character readings (romanized, the ASCII four-way discipline) — not faked.
;
; THE QUALITY CONTRACT — essence, vitality, trust, not equality  (form-stdlib/translation-quality.fk
;   -> tests/translation-quality-band.fk 1111111, four-way)
;   The first A/B (tl-promote?) measured EXACT correctness — wrong for language. The metric
;   Urs named: we don't need 100% equality, we need round-trip ESSENCE capture and VITALITY
;   maintenance; not losing essence, vitality, and TRUST is the key. translation-quality.fk
;   is the corrected gate: the five lenses (lenses.fk) read on the round-trip, accepted when
;   essence (the meaning lens), vitality, and trust stay ABOVE A FLOOR — even if the surface
;   string differs. A different word that keeps the aliveness and the trust passes; an exact-
;   looking word that drops the trust is refused, with the lost lens NAMED (lost-trust,
;   lost-vitality). The round-trip / no-collapse / reciprocal / holdout proof lives in
;   meaning-translation-receipt.fk; this adds the gradient lenses it lacked. And the oracle
;   tiers: bulk (libretranslate) for all, a higher-quality translator spot-checks a sample
;   and improves below-floor pairs; learned pairs cache (no oracle call). The native recipe
;   takes a pair when its round-trip clears the lens floor — vitality preserved, not strings
;   matched.
;
; THE DATA STEP — the zh/ja chrome bundles (named, the carrier-last piece)
;   Adding zh/ja as locales is a pure data operation: drop web/messages/{zh,ja}.json (+ the
;   cli copies), regenerate the manifest (npm run prebuild), pass wellness parity (2019
;   keys, matching en). The strings are the libretranslate ORACLE's output — the same way
;   the existing six non-en bundles were machine-translated, each carrying _attunement
;   metadata that invites human re-attunement. So the oracle's bundle IS the corpus
;   translation-learn.fk trains on, and the native recipe replaces the oracle pair by pair
;   as it proves out. (libretranslate runs in production but not in this local checkout, so
;   the 2019-key generation is the named follow-on, not a hand-faked file — the discipline
;   that held all session: ground the data from the translator, never invent it.)
;
; HONESTY LANES: the native recipe is exact (a learned lookup, content-addressed); the
; oracle's bulk translations are a first pass inviting human attunement; the glyph itself
; rides the oracle until UTF-8 four-way string parity is proven (cjk-channel's named row).
;
; LINEAGE
;   kin: lc-cross-modal-unity (one cell, many tongues — translation IS this), cjk-channel.fk
;        (the proof), loopback-learning.fk / champion-challenger.fk / colearning-retire.fk
;        (the loop and A/B), meaning-translation-receipt.fk (the proof contract), i18n.fk
;        (the corpus), oracle-catalog.fk (where the libretranslate teacher registers next),
;        lenses.fk (sound/symbol media — translation across them), prose-as-recipe.form
;        (the WORD domain: a pair as a content-addressed word-cell edge).
;   source: requested by Urs 2026-06-14; the native side of the locale's translations.
